item.dc:creator: @Redemtion Redemtion
item.description:
@Redemtion wrote:

[quote=“wildskiller, post:21, topic:450248”][quote author=Redemtion link=topic=553144.msg4052975#msg4052975 date=1342683864]
sooo

[code=java]public class ClickObject implements PacketType {

public static final int FIRST_CLICK = 132, SECOND_CLICK = 252, THIRD_CLICK = 70;	
@Override

/*

  • Code in here
    */
    public void handleSpecialCase(Client c, int id, int x, int y) {

    }

}[/code]
Should be like that…?
[/quote]

You don’t put your code between @Override and the overriding method, you put the code inside the overriding method. You only need to add an override if it is really needing to override the super class’s abstract methods.

[code=java]public class ClickObject implements PacketType {

public static final int FIRST_CLICK = 132, SECOND_CLICK = 252, THIRD_CLICK = 70;	

    @Override
public void handleSpecialCase(Client c, int id, int x, int y) {
            /**
             * Code in here
             */
}

}[/code][/quote]
That’s how my server’s set to. Works fine.

item.dc:creator: @mista_pnut mista pnut
item.description:
@mista_pnut wrote:

Rich:

No need to offer a cash reward. All help around here is free.

One of the following reasons is why you are getting this error:

  1. You misspelled the keyword class (fully lower case) or you did not write it at all for writing your class.
  2. Remember you cannot declare variables outside of class body.
  3. All methods are also defined within the method body. If you define any method outside of the class body you will see this error message.
  4. If you are defining an interface, check you spelled it correctly in fully lowercase.
  5. Same way if you define an enum spell the keyword enum correctly.

If all else fails,

lmgtfy.com

LMGTFY

LMGTFY
